Select all the correct statements relating to the following piece of code?
	public class A{
		abstract int method();
		void anotherMethod(){
		}
	class B extends A{
		int method(){
		return 2;
		}
	}
  (i)   Changing "extends" to "implements" on line 6 will allow the code to compile correctly.
  (ii)  The method() in class A cannot be abstract without the entire class being declared as abstract.
  (iii) Declaring class A to be abstract will allow the code to compile correctly.
  (iv)  The class A must have an explicit default constructor in order for it to be subclassed correctly.
  (v)   The code fails to compile, because class B does not implement anotherMethod().

